 <h2>Duo in the Bastion of Thunder</h2><br><br>A lot of people often talk about the effectiveness of soloing in Bastion of Thunder with charm, but it can be very risky.<br><br>A much safer alternative, is to duo with a class that can help you control the charmed pet. This means less wipes, and if your duo class can double up as a really good puller, you wont loose too much exp from soloing.<br><br><br>Before charming your pet, mez it and debuff it with mala and malosinia, and (this is important) get your duo-class to snare it. Then keep your pet parked a way away from where you stand, so that when it breaks you have plenty of time to charm or mez.<br><br><br>As for duo class, I would reccomend a good druid: They can heal, snare, give some crowd control (with root) and pacify-pull. Not to mention you will always have evac and PoTN available. With a good druid, this can considerably outdo full-groups for exp and loot. You can also find places to do this when all the group spots are taken.<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?zone=173'>Bastion of Thunder (BoT) mob list</a><br>
